            , a <rs id="t18270913-112-viclabel643" type="occupation">warehouseman</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18270913-112-victim1200 t18270913-112-viclabel643"></join> - we live in the <placeName id="t18270913-112-crimeloc644">Curtain-road</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18270913-112-crimeloc644" type="placeName" value="Curtain-road"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18270913-112-crimeloc644" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18270913-112-off641 t18270913-112-crimeloc644"></join>, where I keep a milliner's shop. On the 28th of July, about eleven o'clock, I saw my two sovereigns and a sixpence safe in a piece of paper, in the till - I was in the back parlour at half-past twelve o'clock, and heard the lock of the till go - I turned and saw the prisoner with his arms across the counter - I asked what he wanted; he said, "A ready made shirt;" I said, "I keep no such things;" he went out - I looked at the till and missed the money - I ran out caught him, and asked him for the money - he said, he knew nothing about it; I have not found it.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18270913-112-person1203">
                  JOSEPH 
                  BIRCH
               <interp inst="t18270913-112-person1203" type="surname" value="BIRCH"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-112-person1203" type="given" value="JOSEPH"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-112-person1203" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am an officer. I was sent for, and took the prisoner - he said he went in to buy a shirt - he had no money about him, and I said he had no money to pay for it; he said if there had been one to suit him, he should call for it in the evening.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I went in and knocked on the counter; she said she did not sell shirts - she came out and took me, about two yards off - she went back and took out six or seven sovereigns - she said, "These are not what I want;" there were two in a paper.</p>
               <p>
                  <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="182709130084"></xptr>MRS. BREWSTER. There were four other sovereigns in another part of the till - I had not been out of the shop a quarter of an hour.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18270913-112-verdict645" type="verdictDescription">
